               <p>ROBERT THOMAS GRIFFITHS. I am a <rs id="t18270913-262-viclabel1483" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-262-victim2132 t18270913-262-viclabel1483"></join>. On the 12th of September, about half-past two o'clock in the morning, I was at the corner of <placeName id="t18270913-262-crimeloc1484">Pickett-street, Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-262-crimeloc1484" type="placeName" value="Pickett-street, Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-262-crimeloc1484" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-262-off1481 t18270913-262-crimeloc1484"></join>, sleeping; the watchman awoke me, and asked if I had lost any thing; I missed my shoes from my feet, and these other things.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-262-person2133">
                  MICHAEL 
                  BOWER
               <interp inst="t18270913-262-person2133" type="surname" value="BOWER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-262-person2133" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-262-person2133" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. About half-past two o'clock I passed the prisoner, but said nothing to him - he passed me again shortly after - I asked where he was going; he said home - soon after, I saw Griffiths laying down without his shoes, and asked the prisoner where they were - he said he did not know - I took hold of him and found them on him, also the handkerchief and all this property.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been to the play, and found the handkerchief with the things in it - the shoes laid by the parcel.</p>
               <p>
